    },
    {
      "id": "d6a690b7540842b1265659c29b15af01868d3a5f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2015-06-29 07:24:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5: Code-Review+1\n\nOne idea that came to mind while reviewing this is that it probably makes more sense from a protocol point of view to send the XID as part of the ptlrpc_body, and send the matchbits via LNet. That way the XID stays at the ptlrpc protocol level as it really should be, as it doesn't change if the RPC needs to be resent (since the Lustre recovery protocol really depends of the RPC XID staying constant over resend), and the LNet layer can do what it wants with the matchbits if it needs to be resent (e.g. use previous matchbits - 2^30 for each resend, Lustre initializes the matchbits to be at least 2^50 or more).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "20ebf7137fb4299325e62c60c012fe9761b53907",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2015-06-29 08:29:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5: Code-Review+1\n\n(1 comment)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "d3f0ab0417fa6cf91508315f16240edc7203ae14",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 176,
        "name": "Liang Zhen",
        "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
        "username": "liangzhen",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-06-29 12:20:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nAndreas, I actually think both rq_xid and matchbits should be within ptlrpc_body, rq_xid is not really necessary for LNetPut called by ptl_send_rpc()->ptl_send_buf(), from LNet point of view, request portal doesn't need matchbits (reply and bulk portal need matchbits) because RPC can be fit in any request buffer on server and matchbits is ignored.  So the only reason that we transfer rq_xid to LNetPut while sending RPC is, remote peer needs it as matchbits of reply (and bulk without this patch) and identifier of RPC, it means that rq_xid is just a 64-bit data used by ptlrpc, not by LNet.\n\nThe reason that I didn't put rq_xid in ptlrpc_body is because I don't want to consume reserved bytes too quick.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "9a1ecfb893b38aaec3fb0050e68b1ee045ec7716",
